<h1>Problem 22 - 2004 Swedish MO (44th), Final Round, Q4</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>A square with integer side length \(n \geq 3\) is divided into \(n^2\) unit squares, and \(n-1\) lines are drawn so that each square&#x27;s interior is cut by at least one line. <ol><li>Give an example of such a configuration for some \(n\).</li><li>Show that some two of the lines must meet inside the square</li></ol></p>
